1
00:00:00,968 --> 00:00:03,637
♪

2
00:00:05,405 --> 00:00:07,641
Hol horse: Shit,
it’s dark in here.

3
00:00:07,674 --> 00:00:09,643
I can’t see a damn thing.

4
00:00:09,676 --> 00:00:12,145
where the hell
is that bastard, anyway?

5
00:00:13,146 --> 00:00:14,447
( Cloth rustles )

6
00:00:16,483 --> 00:00:18,452
( Growls )

7
00:00:18,485 --> 00:00:20,220
It’s the middle of the day,

8
00:00:20,254 --> 00:00:23,357
and I still have to feel my way
around this hovel.

9
00:00:23,390 --> 00:00:25,259
This had better be worth it.

10
00:00:25,292 --> 00:00:30,063
Okay, if I remember correctly,
i’ll find dio over in that room.

11
00:00:31,064 --> 00:00:32,465
( Gasps )

12
00:00:36,103 --> 00:00:37,471
Ugh! Disgusting.

13
00:00:37,504 --> 00:00:40,173
This little lady must be
one of dio’s leftovers.

14
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:42,676
Damn broads just throw
themselves at the guy,

15
00:00:42,709 --> 00:00:46,079
like having their blood drank
is the latest bedroom craze.

16
00:00:46,113 --> 00:00:48,449
The whole thing’s nutty
if you ask me,

17
00:00:48,482 --> 00:00:51,452
though girls do tend
to go for the bad boys.

18
00:00:51,485 --> 00:00:52,720
But forget about that.

19
00:00:52,753 --> 00:00:54,622
i’ve never seen
so much gold in my life.

20
00:00:54,655 --> 00:00:56,757
How’d he get all this?

21
00:00:56,790 --> 00:01:01,128
Seems like this guy can have
and do just about anything.

22
00:01:01,161 --> 00:01:03,330
♪

23
00:01:06,700 --> 00:01:08,602
Hmm.

24
00:01:08,635 --> 00:01:09,970
Dio: Hol horse...

25
00:01:10,003 --> 00:01:10,971
( Hol horse gasping )

26
00:01:11,004 --> 00:01:13,106
Dio: What is it?

27
00:01:20,447 --> 00:01:24,117
Hol horse: It’s master dio.

28
00:01:24,151 --> 00:01:26,153
( Panting )

29
00:01:30,257 --> 00:01:31,558
Son of a bitch.

30
00:01:31,592 --> 00:01:33,627
What is this?
Just lookin’ at him

31
00:01:33,660 --> 00:01:36,196
is enough to send chills
down my spine.

32
00:01:37,731 --> 00:01:40,167
Keep it together, hol horse.

33
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:42,069
Don’t let him spook you.

34
00:01:42,102 --> 00:01:44,338
he’s nothin’
to lose your cool over.

35
00:01:44,371 --> 00:01:47,507
yeah, he’s not even
that much stronger than you.

36
00:01:47,541 --> 00:01:50,010
Dio: I’ll ask you again.

37
00:01:50,043 --> 00:01:52,746
Did you want something,
hol horse?

38
00:01:52,779 --> 00:01:54,714
Hol horse: Uh,
well, yes, actually.

39
00:01:54,748 --> 00:01:57,084
there’s somethin’
I thought you oughta know.

40
00:01:57,117 --> 00:01:59,553
i received intel
that two of the nine great gods,

41
00:01:59,586 --> 00:02:02,289
mariah and alessi,
have been put out of commission.

42
00:02:02,322 --> 00:02:03,590
Dio: And your point is?

43
00:02:03,624 --> 00:02:06,227
( Hol horse gasps )
Well, there’s more.

44
00:02:06,260 --> 00:02:07,962
We’ve got trouble comin’.

45
00:02:07,995 --> 00:02:11,298
Turns out joestar and his gang
will arrive in Cairo tomorrow,

46
00:02:11,331 --> 00:02:14,067
and only three
of the nine gods are left.

47
00:02:14,101 --> 00:02:16,203
Dio: It seems you’ve
misunderstood my question.

48
00:02:16,236 --> 00:02:18,405
i want to know
what you’re going to do,

49
00:02:18,438 --> 00:02:20,006
- hol horse.
- Hol horse: Eh?!

50
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:22,676
Dio: You seem to have been
caught rather off guard.

51
00:02:22,709 --> 00:02:24,377
I simply wish to know

52
00:02:24,411 --> 00:02:26,146
when you’re going
kill them, hol horse.

53
00:02:26,180 --> 00:02:29,283
while it’s true you’ve
pledged your allegiance to me,

54
00:02:29,316 --> 00:02:33,620
you have yet to adequately
prove yourself in battle.

55
00:02:33,654 --> 00:02:35,389
In this day and age,

56
00:02:35,422 --> 00:02:37,591
any simpleton
can deliver information.

57
00:02:37,624 --> 00:02:42,229
twice you’ve failed me,
and here you are crawling back.

58
00:02:42,262 --> 00:02:44,397
( Hol horse gasping )

59
00:02:49,570 --> 00:02:51,205
( Sizzles )

60
00:02:55,542 --> 00:02:58,245
Dio: You couldn’t know this,
but my body once belonged

61
00:02:58,278 --> 00:03:01,515
to a man by the name
of Jonathan joestar.

62
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:05,052
Jonathan was the grandfather
of Joseph joestar.

63
00:03:05,085 --> 00:03:08,388
look closely.
Notice how the left finger

64
00:03:08,422 --> 00:03:11,125
heals at a slower rate
than the right?

65
00:03:11,158 --> 00:03:14,361
The left side of this body
is weak,

66
00:03:14,394 --> 00:03:18,031
which proves that it doesn’t
completely belong to me yet

67
00:03:18,065 --> 00:03:20,634
and that I am not yet immortal.

68
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:22,602
I am ill-equipped
to fight a battle

69
00:03:22,636 --> 00:03:24,671
with joestar and his friends.

70
00:03:28,609 --> 00:03:31,178
now then,
if there is nothing else,

71
00:03:31,211 --> 00:03:34,381
run along, and destroy
my enemies on my behalf.

72
00:03:34,414 --> 00:03:38,985
Failure will most assuredly
result in your untimely demise.

73
00:03:39,019 --> 00:03:41,421
( Hol horse thinking) You’re
barkin’ up the wrong tree, hoss.

74
00:03:41,455 --> 00:03:43,691
As if threats are
gonna make me roll over

75
00:03:43,724 --> 00:03:45,426
and do whatever you want.

76
00:03:45,459 --> 00:03:48,095
( Growls )
On your behalf, my ass.

77
00:03:48,128 --> 00:03:49,730
I’m no fool.

78
00:03:49,763 --> 00:03:52,432
I’m smart enough to throw in
with whoever’s strongest.

79
00:03:52,466 --> 00:03:55,135
Everything i’ve said
has been lip service.

80
00:03:55,169 --> 00:03:58,506
I’d never swear my loyalty
to you at the cost of my soul.

81
00:03:58,539 --> 00:04:02,043
rat bastard,
you’re not so tough, are you?

82
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,643
You’re wide open.

83
00:04:03,677 --> 00:04:06,246
Guess having another person’s
body attached to your head

84
00:04:06,280 --> 00:04:09,183
has made you go soft.
This is perfect.

85
00:04:09,216 --> 00:04:11,585
I don’t have to fight Joseph
and the other three,

86
00:04:11,618 --> 00:04:14,554
not when i’ve got dio
in my crosshairs.

87
00:04:14,588 --> 00:04:17,691
It’d be a hell of a lot easier
to blow his head to smithereens

88
00:04:17,724 --> 00:04:19,960
right here and now.

89
00:04:19,993 --> 00:04:22,028
♪

90
00:04:22,062 --> 00:04:25,032
If I do, his treasure’s
mine for the takin’.

91
00:04:25,065 --> 00:04:26,934
This’ll be a piece of cake.

92
00:04:26,967 --> 00:04:29,203
He doesn’t know emperor’s
aimed point-blank at his skull.

93
00:04:29,236 --> 00:04:32,072
I could finish him off,
and he’ll be none the wiser.

94
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:36,176
Just one pull of the trigger,
and this nightmare will be over.

95
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:39,513
After all, emperor was made
for close-combat carnage.

96
00:04:39,546 --> 00:04:42,449
I can do this. I can do this.

97
00:04:42,482 --> 00:04:45,652
Dio: Is there a problem?
You seem to be hesitating.

98
00:04:45,686 --> 00:04:47,655
( Hol horse thinking)
Eat lead, shit-bag!

99
00:04:47,688 --> 00:04:49,323
i’m about
to splatter your brains

100
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:52,359
all over the floor, Mr. Dio!

101
00:04:52,392 --> 00:04:55,362
Dio: Are you positive you want
to go through with shooting me?

102
00:04:55,395 --> 00:04:57,364
( Hol horse gasps )

103
00:04:59,666 --> 00:05:01,168
Huh?

104
00:05:01,201 --> 00:05:02,569
He’s gone!

105
00:05:02,603 --> 00:05:03,637
( Dio chuckles )

106
00:05:03,670 --> 00:05:04,905
( Hol horse gasps )

107
00:05:04,938 --> 00:05:06,072
Dio: Fascinating.

108
00:05:06,106 --> 00:05:08,108
As you prepared to fire,

109
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:12,012
your breathing was relaxed.
You didn’t even perspire.

110
00:05:12,045 --> 00:05:13,647
You were composed.

111
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:15,615
Very impressive, hol horse.

112
00:05:23,457 --> 00:05:26,226
( Squelch )

113
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:27,428
( Hol horse gasps )

114
00:05:27,461 --> 00:05:29,263
This doesn’t make
a lick of sense.

115
00:05:29,296 --> 00:05:31,031
I didn’t even see him move.

116
00:05:31,064 --> 00:05:34,167
There’s no way in hell he
could have creeped up behind me

117
00:05:34,201 --> 00:05:36,570
without breaking a single one
of those spider webs.

118
00:05:36,603 --> 00:05:40,140
Fast or not, he shouldn’t have
been able to sneak up to my rear

119
00:05:40,174 --> 00:05:41,375
without me noticing something.

120
00:05:41,408 --> 00:05:44,645
Was that the power
of dio’s stand,

121
00:05:44,678 --> 00:05:46,280
the power of the world?

122
00:05:46,313 --> 00:05:49,583
Ill-equipped? Yeah, right.

123
00:05:49,616 --> 00:05:53,019
I-I finally understand,
master dio.

124
00:05:53,053 --> 00:05:57,190
I’ve got no choice but to pledge
my eternal loyalty to you.

125
00:05:57,224 --> 00:05:59,927
Y-you’ve got me beat.

126
00:06:01,395 --> 00:06:03,397
♪

127
00:06:05,432 --> 00:06:07,434
( Singing in Japanese )

128
00:06:29,489 --> 00:06:31,291
crew member:
Ladies and gentlemen,

129
00:06:31,325 --> 00:06:34,461
we sincerely hope you’ve enjoyed
today’s flight from aswan.

130
00:06:34,495 --> 00:06:36,230
We’ll be arriving on schedule

131
00:06:36,263 --> 00:06:38,699
at Cairo
international airport shortly.

132
00:06:42,536 --> 00:06:45,105
♪

133
00:06:52,646 --> 00:06:55,082
man: Whoops! Snooze,
you loose, buddy! ( Laughs )

134
00:06:55,115 --> 00:06:57,651
man #2: I hate
to break it to you, cowboy,

135
00:06:57,684 --> 00:07:00,387
but it looks like this
is our cab now. ( Laughs )

136
00:07:00,420 --> 00:07:02,489
- No hard feelings?
- ( Hol horse growls )

137
00:07:02,523 --> 00:07:04,291
Man #1: Huh? Don’t tell me

138
00:07:04,324 --> 00:07:06,526
you’re gonna start
cryin’ like a baby! Hah!

139
00:07:08,128 --> 00:07:10,464
( Screaming )

140
00:07:11,698 --> 00:07:14,167
Man #2: Shit! What the hell?!

141
00:07:17,237 --> 00:07:20,340
Hol horse: Giza, pronto.
The mena house hotel.

142
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:29,516
I’m gonna open up this suitcase
and let you out.

143
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:31,252
Unless you want
some grade-a pain,

144
00:07:31,285 --> 00:07:33,220
I suggest you keep calm.
we clear?

145
00:07:33,253 --> 00:07:36,022
Driver: Huh? Did you, uh,
say something just now, sir?

146
00:07:36,056 --> 00:07:38,525
hol horse: If I did,
it sure the hell wasn’t to you.

147
00:07:38,559 --> 00:07:40,294
Now shut up,
and drive the cab!

148
00:07:40,327 --> 00:07:41,528
Driver: Ehh! Yes, sir.

149
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:48,202
( Mondatta grunting )

150
00:07:52,072 --> 00:07:53,407
hol horse:
Cut it out. You know,

151
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,175
if you weren’t
makin’ such a damn racket,

152
00:07:55,209 --> 00:07:56,610
I wouldn’t have had
to hogtie you

153
00:07:56,643 --> 00:07:59,112
and put you on the plane
like a piece of luggage!

154
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:00,948
Don’t be a baby, mondatta.

155
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:02,916
your brother’s got
another month in the hospital

156
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:05,152
thanks to that bomb,
so you and I are partners.

157
00:08:05,185 --> 00:08:06,920
now make sure
those big ears are listening,

158
00:08:06,954 --> 00:08:08,556
’cause here’s
what we’re gonna do.

159
00:08:08,589 --> 00:08:11,926
We’re gonna use your book of
premonitions and my assassin gun

160
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:15,129
to stamp out jotaro, Joseph,
and the rest of those s.O.B.S!

161
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:17,331
Got that, mondatta?!

162
00:08:17,364 --> 00:08:19,199
I get that we haven’t
known each other long,

163
00:08:19,233 --> 00:08:21,035
but from what i’ve gathered,
you’re afraid

164
00:08:21,068 --> 00:08:24,238
of just about anyone that’s
not your brother, zenyatta.

165
00:08:24,271 --> 00:08:26,140
But don’t you think
this is the perfect chance

166
00:08:26,173 --> 00:08:27,441
to avenge the guy?

167
00:08:27,474 --> 00:08:29,009
You don’t wanna be
a yellow-bellied coward

168
00:08:29,042 --> 00:08:31,144
forever, right?
That’s no good.

169
00:08:31,178 --> 00:08:32,680
I’m out of options, too.

170
00:08:32,713 --> 00:08:34,949
We’ve got no choice
but to fight.

171
00:08:34,982 --> 00:08:38,118
time for us
to get our revenge, mondatta.

172
00:08:38,151 --> 00:08:39,552
I’m gonna let you loose now,

173
00:08:39,586 --> 00:08:42,489
but you have to swear to me
you won’t carry on

174
00:08:42,523 --> 00:08:44,458
with all
that infernal hollering, okay?

175
00:08:44,491 --> 00:08:45,459
( Mondatta mutters )

176
00:08:45,492 --> 00:08:46,994
Hol horse: See that, son?

177
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:48,128
I’m not so bad.

178
00:08:48,162 --> 00:08:50,031
Now try and settle down, eh?

179
00:08:50,063 --> 00:08:52,065
I don’t need you
gettin’ sick on me,

180
00:08:52,099 --> 00:08:53,701
’cause believe it or not,

181
00:08:53,734 --> 00:08:55,970
i’m on your side
in this whole mess,

182
00:08:56,003 --> 00:08:59,039
so don’t you worry.
Just relax for now.

183
00:09:02,442 --> 00:09:03,910
Huh?

184
00:09:06,046 --> 00:09:08,081
Driver: Sir, why do you
have a puking kid?!

185
00:09:08,115 --> 00:09:09,316
Hol horse: Shut up!

186
00:09:09,349 --> 00:09:11,418
- ( Mondatta vomits )
- Hol horse: I see.

187
00:09:11,451 --> 00:09:14,087
You got motion sickness
from being on the plane.

188
00:09:14,121 --> 00:09:18,292
mondatta,
l-let’s be pals from here on.

189
00:09:18,325 --> 00:09:19,493
How’s that sound?

190
00:09:19,526 --> 00:09:22,129
( Mondatta vomiting )

191
00:09:23,163 --> 00:09:24,364
"I’m mondatta.

192
00:09:24,398 --> 00:09:26,300
"This is hol horse.

193
00:09:26,333 --> 00:09:28,602
"he’s mean,
and I don’t like him!

194
00:09:28,635 --> 00:09:30,303
"While mondatta was sleeping,

195
00:09:30,337 --> 00:09:32,539
"hol horse tied him up
and stuffed him in a trunk.

196
00:09:32,573 --> 00:09:35,009
"mondatta was taken
from his brother, zenyatta.

197
00:09:35,042 --> 00:09:36,477
"He was sad.

198
00:09:36,510 --> 00:09:39,079
"But even though mondatta
was scared out of his mind,

199
00:09:39,112 --> 00:09:40,680
"he wanted to avenge
his brother,

200
00:09:40,714 --> 00:09:42,549
"so he decided
to work up his courage

201
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:44,919
and become partners
with hol horse."

202
00:09:44,952 --> 00:09:46,554
( Hol horse growls )
hmm?

203
00:09:46,587 --> 00:09:47,555
( Mondatta gasping )

204
00:09:47,588 --> 00:09:48,923
Hol horse: Oh, come on!

205
00:09:48,956 --> 00:09:50,357
You won’t even get near me?

206
00:09:50,390 --> 00:09:51,658
Well, I guess you’re tryin’,

207
00:09:51,692 --> 00:09:54,361
which is all I can
ask for at this point.

208
00:09:54,394 --> 00:09:56,396
And by the way, I gotta know.

209
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:58,432
does your stand
really predict the future,

210
00:09:58,465 --> 00:10:00,567
or is that just
some cockamamie rumor?

211
00:10:00,601 --> 00:10:02,603
If that was all
just a tall tale,

212
00:10:02,636 --> 00:10:04,338
then I brought you here
for nothin’.

213
00:10:04,371 --> 00:10:05,505
I mean, even with it,

214
00:10:05,539 --> 00:10:07,174
your brother
got blown to high heaven.

215
00:10:07,207 --> 00:10:08,975
( Mondatta gasping )

216
00:10:09,009 --> 00:10:12,079
Hol horse: Which is it, kid?!
Are you a fraud?!

217
00:10:12,112 --> 00:10:15,115
Hmm? How’d a new comic

218
00:10:15,148 --> 00:10:17,183
appear on a blank page
from out of nowhere?

219
00:10:17,217 --> 00:10:19,019
mondatta:
"While mondatta and hol horse

220
00:10:19,052 --> 00:10:21,087
"were walking through
the outskirts of Cairo,

221
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:24,091
"they met a lady who was
as pretty as the day was long.

222
00:10:24,124 --> 00:10:27,294
Then hol horse jump-kicked
the lady in the neck!"

223
00:10:27,327 --> 00:10:28,295
Hol horse: Hmm?

224
00:10:28,328 --> 00:10:29,529
Mondatta: "The pretty lady

225
00:10:29,563 --> 00:10:31,398
"was so overjoyed
about the kick that,

226
00:10:31,431 --> 00:10:34,000
"out of the blue,
she gave hol horse her jewels.

227
00:10:34,034 --> 00:10:36,303
Yahoo! We’re rich!"

228
00:10:36,336 --> 00:10:37,704
Hol horse: What the hell

229
00:10:37,738 --> 00:10:39,340
- is this crap?!
- ( Mondatta gulps )

230
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:41,675
Hol horse: You must think
I was born last night!

231
00:10:41,708 --> 00:10:43,243
you call this
a prediction, mondatta?!

232
00:10:43,277 --> 00:10:44,545
There’s just no way!

233
00:10:44,578 --> 00:10:46,980
This crap has to be
made up or somethin’.

234
00:10:47,014 --> 00:10:48,516
Mondatta: I’m telling the truth.

235
00:10:48,549 --> 00:10:52,386
My stand, thoth, you just
have to trust in its prophecies.

236
00:10:52,419 --> 00:10:55,289
Th-th-they’re 100--

237
00:10:55,322 --> 00:10:58,125
they’re 100% right every time.

238
00:10:58,158 --> 00:10:59,459
Hol horse: They’re right 100%?

239
00:10:59,493 --> 00:11:01,662
You tryin’ to pull
the wool over my eyes?!

240
00:11:01,695 --> 00:11:04,198
There’s no way some lady’s
gonna give me her jewels

241
00:11:04,231 --> 00:11:06,066
after jump-kickin’ her
in the neck.

242
00:11:06,099 --> 00:11:09,102
You’d have to be off your rocker
to do somethin’ like that.

243
00:11:09,136 --> 00:11:11,138
Hmm?

244
00:11:11,171 --> 00:11:13,173
♪

245
00:11:14,975 --> 00:11:17,277
( Both gasp )

246
00:11:17,311 --> 00:11:19,547
Hol horse: Listen, mondatta.
I am proud to say

247
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:22,083
that i’m a gentleman
and a proper gentleman at that.

248
00:11:22,115 --> 00:11:24,417
’cause of that, I got girls
all over the world.

249
00:11:24,451 --> 00:11:26,586
I might tell a white lie
now and again,

250
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:28,555
but i’d never haul off
and hit one.

251
00:11:28,589 --> 00:11:30,324
I respect all the ladies,
the beauties,

252
00:11:30,357 --> 00:11:32,426
the plain ones,
and even the ugly ones.

253
00:11:34,695 --> 00:11:37,431
There’s no way your prediction
will ever come to pass.

254
00:11:37,464 --> 00:11:40,701
Come hell or high water, I swear
I will never hit a woman.

255
00:11:40,734 --> 00:11:43,237
She could pay me every dime,
nickel, and quarter she had.

256
00:11:43,270 --> 00:11:45,139
I still wouldn’t
put my hands on her.

257
00:11:45,172 --> 00:11:47,641
Mondatta: It’s 100% true, yes.

258
00:11:47,674 --> 00:11:49,643
( Hol horse growls )

259
00:11:49,676 --> 00:11:51,678
♪

260
00:11:54,147 --> 00:11:55,448
Hmph.

261
00:11:55,482 --> 00:11:57,084
- ( Mondatta whimpers )
- Hol horse: See there?

262
00:11:57,117 --> 00:11:58,352
Your fancy prediction was wrong.

263
00:11:58,385 --> 00:11:59,753
- ( Mondatta whimpering )
- hol horse: Huh?

264
00:11:59,786 --> 00:12:01,721
( Gasping )

265
00:12:10,430 --> 00:12:12,332
( Mondatta grumbles )

266
00:12:12,366 --> 00:12:15,035
( Hol horse yells )

267
00:12:15,068 --> 00:12:16,436
( Woman shrieks )

268
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:18,472
( Man yelps )
Who the hell are you?!

269
00:12:18,505 --> 00:12:20,674
♪

270
00:12:20,707 --> 00:12:22,542
( Woman gasping )

271
00:12:23,544 --> 00:12:25,012
Man: What in the--

272
00:12:25,045 --> 00:12:27,581
th-there was
a scorpion in your shawl!

273
00:12:27,614 --> 00:12:29,950
This thing’s sting
is a death sentence.

274
00:12:29,983 --> 00:12:30,951
Woman: What?!

275
00:12:30,984 --> 00:12:32,686
( Hol horse gasps )

276
00:12:32,719 --> 00:12:34,221
Woman: You spotted
that wretched creature

277
00:12:34,254 --> 00:12:36,423
before it had a chance
to crawl into my clothes.

278
00:12:36,456 --> 00:12:37,657
Man: If you hadn’t killed it,

279
00:12:37,691 --> 00:12:39,459
she would have
been stung for sure.

280
00:12:39,493 --> 00:12:40,461
( Hol horse gasps )

281
00:12:40,494 --> 00:12:41,962
( Mondatta chuckles )

282
00:12:41,995 --> 00:12:43,430
Woman: You saved my life.

283
00:12:43,463 --> 00:12:45,231
Oh, please, let me repay you.

284
00:12:45,265 --> 00:12:47,667
Would my necklace be
a sufficient reward?

285
00:12:47,701 --> 00:12:49,069
It’s yours.

286
00:12:50,137 --> 00:12:51,238
( Hol horse laughs )

287
00:12:51,271 --> 00:12:53,573
Boy, this is my lucky day.

288
00:12:53,607 --> 00:12:56,143
Mondatta and I are
practically invincible.

289
00:12:56,176 --> 00:12:58,011
We’ll be the unstoppable duo!

290
00:13:01,081 --> 00:13:03,383
Roofer: I don’t think i’m
gonna be able to help you folks.

291
00:13:03,417 --> 00:13:06,120
it’s been my job
to repair rooftops in Cairo

292
00:13:06,153 --> 00:13:08,889
for around 40 years now,
and I can’t say

293
00:13:08,922 --> 00:13:11,091
that i’ve ever seen
a place like this.

294
00:13:11,124 --> 00:13:13,026
from the looks
of the building’s design,

295
00:13:13,060 --> 00:13:15,396
the thing was built
over a hundred years ago,

296
00:13:15,429 --> 00:13:16,964
give or take.

297
00:13:16,997 --> 00:13:19,366
If I had to take a guess,
based on the picture,

298
00:13:19,399 --> 00:13:21,501
i’d say you’d find it
somewhere south of here.

299
00:13:21,535 --> 00:13:23,971
The buildings in Cairo
get older and older

300
00:13:24,004 --> 00:13:25,172
the farther south you travel.

301
00:13:25,205 --> 00:13:26,907
Polnareff: Huh?

302
00:13:26,940 --> 00:13:29,443
Roofer: I’m sorry I don’t
have more to go on, Sonny.

303
00:13:29,476 --> 00:13:31,011
polnareff:
No, don’t worry about it.

304
00:13:31,044 --> 00:13:32,012
Sorry to bother.

305
00:13:32,045 --> 00:13:34,214
( Grunts )

306
00:13:34,248 --> 00:13:36,317
( Joseph sighs )

307
00:13:36,350 --> 00:13:37,952
( Grunts )

308
00:13:37,985 --> 00:13:41,388
All right, understood.
Thanks for the update.

309
00:13:44,358 --> 00:13:47,161
I decided to make
a call to Japan,

310
00:13:47,194 --> 00:13:49,430
and my daughter’s condition
is much worse.

311
00:13:49,463 --> 00:13:51,632
She’s lost virtually
all of her strength.

312
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:54,368
at best, she has
three or four days left.

313
00:13:54,401 --> 00:13:55,302
( Both gasp )

314
00:13:55,335 --> 00:13:57,304
( Jotaro sighs )

315
00:13:57,337 --> 00:13:59,272
( Joseph sighs )

316
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,576
I can almost feel it.

317
00:14:02,609 --> 00:14:04,978
It’s like dio’s
right on top of us.

318
00:14:05,012 --> 00:14:07,948
I’d bet anything that he’s
hiding somewhere close by,

319
00:14:07,981 --> 00:14:11,418
but where could he be,
and how do we find him?

320
00:14:11,451 --> 00:14:12,986
Avdol: We should get moving.

321
00:14:13,020 --> 00:14:15,089
We’ll talk to everyone here
until we find him.

322
00:14:15,122 --> 00:14:17,524
joseph: Hmm.
We’ve come this far.

323
00:14:17,558 --> 00:14:19,627
We have to keep going.

324
00:14:24,565 --> 00:14:27,001
♪

325
00:14:27,034 --> 00:14:28,369
hol horse:
Been a long time comin’,

326
00:14:28,402 --> 00:14:30,204
but it’s time
for our grand reunion.

327
00:14:30,237 --> 00:14:32,106
I’m getting sick of those faces.

328
00:14:32,139 --> 00:14:34,975
I never thought they’d get so
close to master dio’s mansion,

329
00:14:35,008 --> 00:14:37,077
but they’re on a collision
course for his backyard.

330
00:14:37,110 --> 00:14:39,379
And by the way,
listen, mondatta!

331
00:14:40,547 --> 00:14:42,215
( Mondatta yelps )

332
00:14:42,249 --> 00:14:44,251
( Whimpering )

333
00:14:46,153 --> 00:14:48,622
Hol horse: We need to chat
about your latest prediction.

334
00:14:48,655 --> 00:14:50,924
You sure it’s 100% foolproof?

335
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:52,426
It’s more than a little wacky.

336
00:14:52,459 --> 00:14:54,528
They’re not dumb enough
to fall for this.

337
00:14:54,561 --> 00:14:56,029
( Mondatta whimpers )

338
00:14:56,063 --> 00:14:58,132
B-but my premonitions--ow!

339
00:14:58,165 --> 00:15:01,135
Hol horse: "My premonitions
are always 100% accurate."

340
00:15:01,168 --> 00:15:02,569
Is that what you were gonna say?

341
00:15:02,603 --> 00:15:04,371
Mondatta: Well, they are, yes.

342
00:15:04,404 --> 00:15:05,906
Hol horse: Come on!

343
00:15:05,939 --> 00:15:08,041
you really expect me
to buy this load of baloney?

344
00:15:08,075 --> 00:15:09,476
I think you’ve lost
your touch, boy.

345
00:15:09,510 --> 00:15:12,413
"’we found them!’
shouted hol horse.

346
00:15:12,446 --> 00:15:15,516
"’joseph, jotaro,
polnareff, and avdol.

347
00:15:15,549 --> 00:15:17,251
"Darn it,’ hol horse fumed.

348
00:15:17,284 --> 00:15:18,619
"’they’re a hop,
skip, and a jump

349
00:15:18,652 --> 00:15:20,521
"’away from master dio’s manor.

350
00:15:20,554 --> 00:15:23,290
Those nosy buffoons’ll each
get a bullet between the eyes.’"

351
00:15:23,323 --> 00:15:25,992
mondatta: "Hol horse’s mind
was full of violent thoughts.

352
00:15:26,026 --> 00:15:28,295
"’you’re gonna pay
for my brother!’

353
00:15:28,328 --> 00:15:30,664
"mondatta was beside himself
with anger.

354
00:15:30,697 --> 00:15:33,266
"But despite the pair
wanting immediate payback,

355
00:15:33,300 --> 00:15:36,503
hol horse couldn’t use his gun,
the emperor, in the market."

356
00:15:38,539 --> 00:15:40,941
"’now, hol horse,’
mondatta instructed,

357
00:15:40,974 --> 00:15:43,510
"’stick your fingers
all the way up polnareff’s nose,

358
00:15:43,544 --> 00:15:45,446
"’and then we’ll win!

359
00:15:45,479 --> 00:15:47,648
"’they’re out cold
from losing all that blood.

360
00:15:47,681 --> 00:15:49,316
"’lucky you, hol horse.

361
00:15:49,349 --> 00:15:52,118
this is your chance
to finish them off for good.’"

362
00:15:52,152 --> 00:15:54,187
hol horse: Like hell
i’m gonna buy that!

363
00:15:54,221 --> 00:15:56,557
This is your big premonition?

364
00:15:56,590 --> 00:15:58,325
Sticking my calloused fingers

365
00:15:58,358 --> 00:16:00,327
up polnareff’s
booger-infested nose?

366
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:03,597
The hell do you take me for?
Well, speak, mondatta!

367
00:16:03,630 --> 00:16:05,866
The part about killing ’em
sounds good to me,

368
00:16:05,899 --> 00:16:07,334
but the rest of it--

369
00:16:07,367 --> 00:16:09,402
you’d better not be planning
anything funny, boy.

370
00:16:09,436 --> 00:16:11,505
I mean, come on! Even if I was

371
00:16:11,538 --> 00:16:13,640
supposed to stick my fingers
up polnareff’s nose,

372
00:16:13,674 --> 00:16:16,343
i’d have to somehow get
close enough to him to do it.

373
00:16:17,544 --> 00:16:19,346
instead of
all that skullduggery,

374
00:16:19,379 --> 00:16:21,314
I think we should go
with the direct approach

375
00:16:21,348 --> 00:16:24,084
and put a bullet in him
with emperor! What do you say?

376
00:16:24,117 --> 00:16:27,420
Mondatta: Y-you’re not gonna
be able to fire a bullet, yes.

377
00:16:27,454 --> 00:16:29,523
E-even though you tried
firing your stand,

378
00:16:29,556 --> 00:16:32,092
fate wouldn’t let you, yes.

379
00:16:32,125 --> 00:16:33,893
You have to trust me, yes.

380
00:16:33,927 --> 00:16:35,061
I know from personal experience,

381
00:16:35,095 --> 00:16:37,297
I-If you try to go
against the comic,

382
00:16:37,331 --> 00:16:38,399
you’ll suffer the consequences.

383
00:16:38,432 --> 00:16:39,934
It’s fate, I tell you.

384
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:42,336
it’s 100%
up to the whims of fate, yes.

385
00:16:42,369 --> 00:16:43,670
Hol horse: Hang on!

386
00:16:43,704 --> 00:16:45,940
Your brother followed the comic
and nearly died.

387
00:16:45,973 --> 00:16:49,910
Mondatta: M-my brother
was trying to save himself,

388
00:16:49,943 --> 00:16:52,012
but he foolishly
disguised himself as jotaro

389
00:16:52,045 --> 00:16:53,513
without thinking, yes.

390
00:16:53,547 --> 00:16:56,350
If he had trusted what he read
and not disguised himself,

391
00:16:56,383 --> 00:16:58,919
then the real jotaro
would have been blown up, yes.

392
00:16:58,952 --> 00:17:02,322
The premonition itself
was correct, yes.

393
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:03,557
( Hol horse groans )

394
00:17:03,590 --> 00:17:05,025
Then what now?

395
00:17:05,058 --> 00:17:06,026
Hmm?

396
00:17:06,059 --> 00:17:08,395
Wait! Where did polnareff go?

397
00:17:08,428 --> 00:17:10,864
hey, kid,
polnareff left the herd.

398
00:17:10,898 --> 00:17:12,400
Find out where he went.

399
00:17:12,432 --> 00:17:13,433
( Mondatta gasps )

400
00:17:13,467 --> 00:17:16,136
Hol horse: Shit! It can’t be.

401
00:17:17,204 --> 00:17:18,439
Polnareff: Don’t you move...

402
00:17:18,472 --> 00:17:20,941
Unless you’d like to be lanced.

403
00:17:20,974 --> 00:17:24,244
hol horse:
But how the hell did you...

404
00:17:28,649 --> 00:17:31,318
( Gags )

405
00:17:31,351 --> 00:17:33,486
Polnareff: Imbecile!
What exactly did you think

406
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,322
you were trying
to pull just now?

407
00:17:35,355 --> 00:17:36,623
If you know what’s good for you,

408
00:17:36,657 --> 00:17:38,325
keep your hands
where I can see them.

409
00:17:38,358 --> 00:17:39,993
( Hol horse groaning )

410
00:17:40,027 --> 00:17:42,429
polnareff: I thought
I noticed someone stalking us

411
00:17:42,462 --> 00:17:44,264
like a desperate,
starving hyena,

412
00:17:44,298 --> 00:17:46,100
and wouldn’t you know,
I was lucky enough

413
00:17:46,133 --> 00:17:48,502
to stumble across
our old friend, hol horse.

414
00:17:48,535 --> 00:17:50,937
it looks you’re
still trying to kill us,

415
00:17:50,971 --> 00:17:53,307
which means you haven’t
learned your lesson yet.

416
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:56,143
Say, thanks for all
the fun back in India.

417
00:17:56,176 --> 00:17:58,378
you’re very lucky
avdol survived our run-in,

418
00:17:58,412 --> 00:17:59,847
’cause if he hadn’t,

419
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:02,883
you, my friend,
would already be dead.

420
00:18:02,916 --> 00:18:04,050
( Hol horse grunting )

421
00:18:04,084 --> 00:18:06,386
polnareff:
You here alone, hol horse?

422
00:18:06,420 --> 00:18:09,857
No way. A coward like you
wouldn’t come by himself.

423
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:12,926
I’m sure he’s hiding out
nearby, right?

424
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:14,528
Well, where’s your partner?

425
00:18:14,561 --> 00:18:17,164
Hol horse: Crap!
On the upside, though,

426
00:18:17,197 --> 00:18:21,068
he hasn’t noticed mondatta yet.
I still have a chance.

427
00:18:21,101 --> 00:18:23,136
( Gasps )

428
00:18:23,170 --> 00:18:25,072
Shit!

429
00:18:25,105 --> 00:18:27,574
He’s gonna see the book
and his fingers.

430
00:18:27,608 --> 00:18:30,311
Polnareff: On your own, you’re
not much of a threat, hol horse,

431
00:18:30,344 --> 00:18:31,512
but i’m well aware
that you have

432
00:18:31,545 --> 00:18:34,248
a special talent
for picking allies.

433
00:18:34,281 --> 00:18:36,517
If you’ve found someone
to work with like before,

434
00:18:36,550 --> 00:18:38,619
that could make you
a dangerous obstacle.

435
00:18:38,652 --> 00:18:40,954
tell me,
where did your partner go?

436
00:18:40,988 --> 00:18:43,891
out with it.
Where is the other stand user?

437
00:18:43,924 --> 00:18:45,092
Hol horse: Your fingers.

438
00:18:45,125 --> 00:18:47,194
Mondatta, hide your fingers.

439
00:18:47,227 --> 00:18:50,897
if he gets wise
to where you are, it’s all over.

440
00:18:50,931 --> 00:18:52,332
Mondatta: You have to believe.

441
00:18:52,366 --> 00:18:54,134
the reason
you’re in this situation

442
00:18:54,168 --> 00:18:56,303
is because
you tried using your gun.

443
00:18:56,336 --> 00:18:58,138
Trust me. Believe in fate.

444
00:18:58,172 --> 00:19:00,107
If you believe
in the power of fate,

445
00:19:00,140 --> 00:19:02,509
our victory is guaranteed, yes.

446
00:19:04,478 --> 00:19:05,879
- Polnareff: Hmm?
- Hol horse: Huh?

447
00:19:07,114 --> 00:19:09,283
Polnareff: I saw a hand
go under the box,

448
00:19:09,316 --> 00:19:10,951
which means my hunch was right.

449
00:19:10,984 --> 00:19:12,385
Avdol: What’s the word,
polnareff?

450
00:19:12,419 --> 00:19:15,155
Did you find the guy
that was following us?

451
00:19:15,189 --> 00:19:19,493
Hol horse: Oh, no, it’s avdol,
and he’s headed straight for us.

452
00:19:19,526 --> 00:19:21,361
Mondatta: Believe, yes.

453
00:19:21,395 --> 00:19:23,364
Put your faith in the book,

454
00:19:23,397 --> 00:19:26,267
and stick your fingers
up polnareff’s nose, yes!

455
00:19:26,300 --> 00:19:28,002
Hol horse: Are you serious?

456
00:19:28,035 --> 00:19:29,470
Damn it.

457
00:19:29,503 --> 00:19:31,538
- Joseph: Hmm?
- Avdol: Hmm?

458
00:19:31,572 --> 00:19:33,641
( Hol horse gasps )
I’ve got no choice.

459
00:19:33,674 --> 00:19:35,209
Fine. I’ll do it!

460
00:19:35,242 --> 00:19:37,077
♪

461
00:19:37,110 --> 00:19:38,912
Polnareff: You under the crate,
show yourself!

462
00:19:38,946 --> 00:19:41,081
Hol horse: Now, while he’s
looking the other way!

463
00:19:41,114 --> 00:19:42,649
polnareff: I know
you’re hiding under there!

464
00:19:46,386 --> 00:19:47,954
What the hell?!

465
00:19:47,988 --> 00:19:49,923
Hol horse: Hell, yeah!

466
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:55,229
( Polnareff gasping )

467
00:19:55,262 --> 00:19:56,630
( Mondatta chuckles )

468
00:19:56,663 --> 00:19:59,432
"’whoo-hoo!
Everyone bled so much,

469
00:19:59,466 --> 00:20:02,069
"’they all passed out!
Lucky you, hol horse!

470
00:20:02,102 --> 00:20:04,438
Now’s your chance
to finish them off!’"

471
00:20:04,471 --> 00:20:06,573
hol horse: So when is
this so-called chance

472
00:20:06,607 --> 00:20:09,443
supposed to get here,
and what do I do ’til then?

473
00:20:09,476 --> 00:20:12,045
Polnareff: Excuse me, hol horse.

474
00:20:12,079 --> 00:20:14,214
Uh, what the hell
are you doing?

475
00:20:14,248 --> 00:20:15,649
hol horse:
You’re not the only one

476
00:20:15,682 --> 00:20:17,684
who wants to know
the answer to that question.

477
00:20:17,718 --> 00:20:20,154
I haven’t the foggiest idea
where to go from here.

478
00:20:20,187 --> 00:20:23,157
What am I supposed to do?

479
00:20:23,190 --> 00:20:24,925
avdol: Hey,
what’s the matter, polnareff?

480
00:20:24,958 --> 00:20:26,226
( Hol horse gasps )

481
00:20:26,260 --> 00:20:28,362
Avdol: He’s not answering back.

482
00:20:28,395 --> 00:20:29,496
Jotaro: Something’s off.

483
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,998
Hol horse: Shit! What now?!

484
00:20:31,031 --> 00:20:32,933
They’re on me
like white on rice!

485
00:20:32,966 --> 00:20:34,634
Damn it! How the hell

486
00:20:34,668 --> 00:20:38,038
do I make the rest of this
stupid prediction come true?

487
00:20:38,071 --> 00:20:40,140
This is crazy.

488
00:20:40,174 --> 00:20:42,510
What am I supposed to do?!

489
00:20:43,577 --> 00:20:46,380
♪

490
00:20:46,413 --> 00:20:48,248
( Singing and speaking
in Japanese )

